Terrance and Phillip travel to Iran to rescue Terrance's daughter, Sally, who is being held prisoner by Iranian cops. A complex chain of events involving a female pop vocalist, a middle eastern dictator and chemical warfare leads to a hostile takeover of Canada. Terrance and Phillip attempts to save Sally and their home country.

When Barbrady resigns and anarchy ensues, the mayor orders Barbrady to go back to school and the boys pitch in to help. Meanwhile, Cartman brings his own brand of law to the streets of South Park.
